  <body>
    <p  style="width: 70%"> The Silicon Radar Eval Board WebGUI is an Html- and
      JavaScript-based Interface to visualize data coming from the Silicon Radar
      Eval Board using an ASCII-based Protocol. The WebGUI uses a <a  href="https://developer.mozilla.org/en-US/docs/Web/API/WebSockets_API/Writing_WebSocket_client_applications">Websocket-</a>
      Connection to communicate with the Server and was developed and tested on
      Chrome and Firefox.</p>
    <b>
      <p  style="width: 70%">The following Opensource-JavaScript-Frameworks have
        been used to develop the WebGUI:</p>
      <table  style="width: 90%;"  border="0">
        <tbody>
          <tr>
            <td>jquery.js</td>
            <td><a  href="https://jquery.com/">https://jquery.com/</a><br>
            </td>
            <td><br>
            </td>
            <td><br>
            </td>
          </tr>
          <tr>
            <td>three.js</td>
            <td> <a  href="http://threejs.org">http://three.js</a></td>
            <td>A Javascript-Framework for creating WebGL content<br>
            </td>
            <td>used for the 3D- Visualization</td>
          </tr>
          <tr>
            <td> dat.gui</td>
            <td><a  href="https://github.com/dataarts/dat.gui">https://github.com/dataarts/dat.gui</a></td>
            <td>A lightweight graphical user interface for changing variables in
              JavaScript. </td>
            <td>used for Cameracontrols</td>
          </tr>
          <tr>
            <td>d3.js</td>
            <td><a  href="https://d3js.org/">https://d3js.org/</a></td>
            <td>JavaScript library for manipulating documents based on data. </td>
            <td>used for the Phase-Diagramm</td>
          </tr>
        </tbody>
      </table>
      <br>
      <br>
      The Web-GUI consists of the Files: index.html, style.css and the following
      JavaScript-Files: <br>
      <br>
      <table  style="width: 100%;"  border="0">
        <tbody>
            <tr>
            <td><a  href="#"  onclick="showindexDoc()"  ;="">index.html</a></td>
            <td>the html-site to be displayed, where all content is inside</td>
          </tr>
          <tr>
            <td><a  href="#"  onclick="showStyleCSSDoc()"  ;="">style.css</a></td>
            <td>the css-file for styling the html-elements in the index.html</td>
          </tr>
          <tr>
            <td><a  href="#"  onclick="showglobalsDoc()"  ;="">globals.js</a></td>
            <td>contains all global variables</td>
          </tr>
          <tr>
            <td><a  href="#"  onclick="showscreen1sDoc();">screen1.js</a></td>
            <td>script for initializing the three.js scene and for adding
              objects the scene</td>
          </tr>
          <tr>
            <td><a  href="#"  onclick="showconnectionDoc();">connection.js</a></td>
            <td>script for communication with the server, opens a websocket
              connection</td>
          </tr>
          <tr>
            <td><a  href="#"  onclick="showcontrolssDoc();">controls.js</a></td>
            <td>contains the functions to control the GUI</td>
          </tr>
          <tr>
            <td><a  href="#"  onclick="showcameracontrolsDoc();">cameracontrols.js</a></td>
            <td>contains the functions to control the camera</td>
          </tr>
          <tr>
              <td><a  href="#"  onclick="//showloggingDoc();">logging.js</a></td>
              <td>contains the funtions for the Log</td>
          </tr>
        </tbody>
      </table>
      <br>
      <br>
    </b>
  </body>
